00:49:41,633 --> 00:49:43,067
Well, what do you think?

790
00:49:44,267 --> 00:49:45,533
Very nice.

791
00:49:46,500 --> 00:49:48,133
Shall I wrap these
up for you then?

792
00:49:58,600 --> 00:49:59,800
That matches better.

793
00:49:59,833 --> 00:50:01,133
-Like right there.
-All right. Okay...

794
00:50:01,167 --> 00:50:02,400
-(phone ringing)
-Okay. Want me to get that?

795
00:50:02,433 --> 00:50:03,500
Mm-hmm.

796
00:50:06,800 --> 00:50:08,833
Olivia Jordan's.
May I help you?

797
00:50:08,867 --> 00:50:11,367
Steven: Hello, Marge. 
 Is my wife in?

798
00:50:11,400 --> 00:50:12,600
It's for you.

799
00:50:14,733 --> 00:50:15,767
Hello?

800
00:50:15,800 --> 00:50:17,000
Well, hello.

801
00:50:17,033 --> 00:50:18,067
What are you doing?

802
00:50:18,900 --> 00:50:21,967
-Right now?
 -No, next August.

803
00:50:22,000 --> 00:50:23,333
Max, what's going on?

804
00:50:23,367 --> 00:50:24,633
Well, why don't
you take a little walk

805
00:50:24,667 --> 00:50:26,033
to your window and see.

806
00:50:30,433 --> 00:50:33,400
-Not too shabby, huh?
-Oh, Max.

807
00:50:33,433 --> 00:50:35,067
You closed the Russo deal!

808
00:50:35,100 --> 00:50:36,400
Better. Better.

809
00:50:36,433 --> 00:50:38,533
What could be better
than closing the Russo deal?

810
00:50:38,567 --> 00:50:40,100
Would you just get
down here, please?

811
00:50:40,133 --> 00:50:41,200
I'm paying by the hour.

812
00:50:41,233 --> 00:50:42,733
Okay. Okay. Okay.

813
00:50:44,100 --> 00:50:47,233
Marge, will you, uh,
close up for me, okay?

814
00:50:47,267 --> 00:50:48,300
Sure.

815
00:50:55,067 --> 00:50:57,900
-Olivia: What is all this?
-Steven: This is a toast,

816
00:50:57,933 --> 00:51:00,800
because three years ago today
I asked you to marry me.

817
00:51:00,833 --> 00:51:02,067
And I have been...

818
00:51:03,567 --> 00:51:05,467
...miserably happy ever since.

819
00:51:05,500 --> 00:51:07,067
Three years ago today?

820
00:51:07,100 --> 00:51:08,933
Mm-hmm. March 20th.

821
00:51:08,967 --> 00:51:10,367
April 20th.

822
00:51:11,167 --> 00:51:13,467
Well, that's not
what I remember.

823
00:51:13,500 --> 00:51:15,967
Max, I'm telling you,
it was April 20th.

824
00:51:16,067 --> 00:51:18,433
Remember the baseball game?
We were incredibly cold

825
00:51:18,467 --> 00:51:19,767
but you insisted that
we get ice cream,

826
00:51:19,800 --> 00:51:21,767
so I did.
And then when I opened the lid

827
00:51:21,800 --> 00:51:23,867
that's where I found the ring,
stuck in the ice cream.

828
00:51:23,900 --> 00:51:25,333
Does that ring
any bells for you?

829
00:51:26,233 --> 00:51:27,367
Don't you remember that?

830
00:51:29,767 --> 00:51:31,333
Sorta. Yeah...

831
00:51:32,067 --> 00:51:33,300
Remember how amazed we were

832
00:51:33,333 --> 00:51:34,967
that the ice cream vendor
didn't steal the ring?

833
00:51:36,233 --> 00:51:36,733
Yep.

834
00:51:37,867 --> 00:51:40,833
Baseball season doesn't
even start till April, Max.

835
00:51:42,600 --> 00:51:43,667
Yeah...

836
00:51:44,400 --> 00:51:45,500
I... I don't ...

837
00:51:46,200 --> 00:51:47,367
I don't know what to say.

838
00:51:48,467 --> 00:51:50,400
I guess that means that you,

839
00:51:50,433 --> 00:51:52,533
uh, probably won't be
wanting this then, huh?

840
00:51:54,367 --> 00:51:55,533
Oh...

841
00:51:56,233 --> 00:51:57,367
(gasps)

842
00:51:58,867 --> 00:52:00,500
Oh, it's beautiful.

843
00:52:02,233 --> 00:52:03,867
Oh, Max...
(chuckles)

844
00:52:05,667 --> 00:52:06,933
Can we afford this?

845
00:52:08,133 --> 00:52:09,600
Baby, after tomorrow night,

846
00:52:10,567 --> 00:52:13,067
you'll never have to ask
that question again.

847
00:52:25,667 --> 00:52:26,800
-Hi.
-Good evening.

848
00:52:26,833 --> 00:52:28,600
-Reservations for...
-Jordan.

849
00:52:30,200 --> 00:52:32,467
You're Max, right? Max Jordan?

850
00:52:32,500 --> 00:52:34,533
-Yeah.
-You're Stu Fishman's friend?

851
00:52:34,567 --> 00:52:36,167
Right. Right. Right.

852
00:52:36,200 --> 00:52:37,300
Why don't I show
you to your table?

853
00:52:37,333 --> 00:52:38,700
Thank you.

854
00:52:38,733 --> 00:52:40,067
Stu Fishman's friend?

855
00:52:40,100 --> 00:52:43,667
(piano music plays
in background)

856
00:52:53,633 --> 00:52:55,567
-Hostess: Enjoy your dinner.
-Thank you.

857
00:52:55,600 --> 00:52:57,767
Olivia: So, you came here
with Stu Fishman?

858
00:52:57,800 --> 00:52:59,533
Yeah, we had a
quick drink after work.

859
00:52:59,567 --> 00:53:00,800
Why didn't you tell me about it?

860
00:53:00,833 --> 00:53:02,800
I didn't think it was
worth mentioning.

861
00:53:02,833 --> 00:53:06,600
Max, the guy sneezes at work
and you tell me about it.

862
00:53:06,633 --> 00:53:08,100
Well, I guess I forgot.

863
00:53:08,133 --> 00:53:10,067
-Does it matter?
-No. It's just

864
00:53:10,067 --> 00:53:11,300
you can't stand him.

865
00:53:11,333 --> 00:53:13,333
You never socialize with him...

866
00:53:13,367 --> 00:53:14,833
You're even talking about
leaving the company

867
00:53:14,867 --> 00:53:17,067
and all of a sudden
you're drinking buddies?

868
00:53:17,067 --> 00:53:18,400
It was one drink.

869
00:53:28,433 --> 00:53:31,567
All right.
I'm gonna come clean with you.

870
00:53:31,600 --> 00:53:34,533
I'm seeing Stu Fishman.
I think it's serious.

871
00:53:34,567 --> 00:53:35,700
-Max...
-What?

872
00:53:35,733 --> 00:53:37,800
What is the big deal?

873
00:53:37,833 --> 00:53:38,967
Ah, come on, Liv.

874
00:53:39,067 --> 00:53:41,667
This is supposed to be
a celebration, remember?

875
00:53:41,700 --> 00:53:42,067
Of what?

876
00:53:43,300 --> 00:53:45,233
The two year and eleven month
anniversary of our engagement?

877
00:53:47,467 --> 00:53:49,500
And why do you keep
calling me Liv all the time?

878
00:53:49,533 --> 00:53:50,933
You know how much I hate that.

879
00:53:55,133 --> 00:53:56,667
I screwed up the date.

880
00:53:56,700 --> 00:53:58,467
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

881
00:53:59,400 --> 00:54:01,467
Please, that's not
what I'm talking about.

882
00:54:03,567 --> 00:54:04,633
Max...

883
00:54:05,700 --> 00:54:06,833
...maybe it's me...

884
00:54:08,333 --> 00:54:09,533
...but ever since
Uncle Len died,

885
00:54:09,567 --> 00:54:11,267
you've been acting like
a different person.

886
00:54:14,500 --> 00:54:17,667
Len and Ruth were happy, hmm?
They had it all.

887
00:54:17,700 --> 00:54:18,933
The next thing we know,

888
00:54:18,967 --> 00:54:20,867
he shoots himself
and she's in the hospital.

889
00:54:20,900 --> 00:54:23,467
That is a tragedy,
and you and I both know that.

890
00:54:23,500 --> 00:54:26,433
It's also a reality.
And we must face that!

891
00:54:27,700 --> 00:54:28,800
Now I am not gonna sit around

892
00:54:28,833 --> 00:54:30,533
for the rest of my life
and be miserable.

893
00:54:30,567 --> 00:54:31,833
And if you think I am,

894
00:54:31,867 --> 00:54:33,433
well maybe you don't
know me very well at all.

895
00:54:33,467 --> 00:54:34,900
I'm going back to the apartment.

896
00:54:44,967 --> 00:54:46,167
(door slams)

897
00:54:53,433 --> 00:54:55,700
You screwed me
on the anniversary, Max.

898
00:54:55,733 --> 00:54:56,800
It's April 20th.

899
00:54:57,833 --> 00:54:59,767
No, no. It's April.

900
00:54:59,800 --> 00:55:02,633
Not March, not May, but April.

901
00:55:02,667 --> 00:55:04,600
I just went through a
whole argument about it.

902
00:55:04,633 --> 00:55:06,167
And she hates the name Liv, too.

903
00:55:06,200 --> 00:55:08,067
Or are you too stupid to
remember that?

904
00:55:13,433 --> 00:55:14,600
It's gonna cost you, Max.

905
00:55:15,733 --> 00:55:17,167
Remember our deal?

906
00:55:17,200 --> 00:55:18,233
Any mistakes you make,

907
00:55:18,267 --> 00:55:20,433
someone you care
about dies? Hmm?

908
00:55:20,467 --> 00:55:21,633
Remember that?

909
00:55:21,667 --> 00:55:23,133
(siren wails in distance)

910
00:55:27,267 --> 00:55:28,733
Who do you think it
might be? Hmm?

911
00:55:29,767 --> 00:55:32,800
Well, you'll have plenty
of time to ponder that.

912
00:55:32,833 --> 00:55:35,067
If I get a chance
I'll take some photos.

913
00:55:35,067 --> 00:55:36,767
We can play a little
show and tell.

914
00:55:42,633 --> 00:55:44,600
(indistinct chatter
in background)

915
00:55:51,100 --> 00:55:53,200
(alarm blaring)

916
00:55:53,233 --> 00:55:54,467
Man: Get dressed.
Let's go!

917
00:55:54,500 --> 00:55:56,200
Woman (over tannoy):
 Code blue, Unit One.

918
00:55:56,233 --> 00:55:58,067
Code blue, Unit One.

919
00:55:58,067 --> 00:56:00,267
(indistinct conversations
in background)

920
00:56:00,300 --> 00:56:01,800
Woman: I'm right behind you.
Let's go.

921
00:56:01,833 --> 00:56:04,467
(indistinct, overlapping
conversations)

922
00:56:07,167 --> 00:56:08,933
(alarm stops)

923
00:56:10,267 --> 00:56:13,067
(monitor bleeping steadily)

924
00:56:28,500 --> 00:56:29,767
(knocking at door)

925
00:56:31,100 --> 00:56:32,733
Did you call
the hospital back?

926
00:56:33,600 --> 00:56:34,967
No, not yet.

927
00:56:35,067 --> 00:56:37,367
You should.
It sounded important.

928
00:56:37,400 --> 00:56:38,900
Hey, Max,
I just got off the phone

929
00:56:38,933 --> 00:56:40,200
with Russo and he's
throwing numbers at me.

930
00:56:40,233 --> 00:56:41,300
I don't know
whether he's talking about

931
00:56:41,333 --> 00:56:43,300
triple net deal,
gross lease or what.

932
00:56:43,333 --> 00:56:44,700
What's the story?

933
00:56:44,733 --> 00:56:46,600
I haven't had time to
hammer out those details yet.

934
00:56:46,633 --> 00:56:49,100
Not according to
the last contract I typed.

935
00:56:49,133 --> 00:56:51,267
-Well, which is...?
-Triple net.

936
00:56:51,300 --> 00:56:53,433
Well, it better be because
that's a deal-breaker.

937
00:56:53,467 --> 00:56:55,367
No, it's definitely triple net.
Don't worry.

938
00:56:55,400 --> 00:56:56,933
I worry. I get paid to worry.

939
00:56:56,967 --> 00:56:59,067
Otherwise Stu comes down on me
about worrying all the time--

940
00:56:59,100 --> 00:57:02,100
Scarlett's right.
It's been triple net all along.

941
00:57:02,133 --> 00:57:03,200
I'll call Russo on it.

942
00:57:04,067 --> 00:57:05,100
Okay.

943
00:57:06,933 --> 00:57:08,067
(phone ringing)

944
00:57:08,867 --> 00:57:10,067
I'll get that.

945
00:57:11,800 --> 00:57:13,167
Max Jordan's office.

946
00:57:13,200 --> 00:57:14,567
Uh, Scarlett, it's Olivia.

947
00:57:15,567 --> 00:57:17,300
Oh, hey, hon. How are ya?

948
00:57:17,333 --> 00:57:18,933
Uh, Ruth...
Ruth died.

949
00:57:18,967 --> 00:57:20,200
Can you put Max on?

950
00:57:21,567 --> 00:57:22,733
It's Olivia.

951
00:57:25,267 --> 00:57:26,333
I'll be outside.

952
00:57:33,400 --> 00:57:34,733
Hey, what's going on?

953
00:57:34,767 --> 00:57:36,167
Max, I... I...

954
00:57:36,200 --> 00:57:37,233
Steven:
 What is it? What's wrong?

955
00:57:38,967 --> 00:57:40,100
It's Ruth.

956
00:57:40,133 --> 00:57:41,667
I just got a call
from the hospital...

957
00:57:44,333 --> 00:57:46,533
She died in her
sleep last night.

958
00:57:46,567 --> 00:57:47,767
Oh, no.

959
00:57:48,867 --> 00:57:50,367
Olivia:
 She had some kind of arrest.

960
00:57:51,500 --> 00:57:53,733
But they said
she was getting better.

961
00:57:53,767 --> 00:57:55,600
Oh, honey, I'm so sorry.

962
00:57:56,700 --> 00:57:58,267
You wanna meet me
back at the house?

963
00:57:58,300 --> 00:57:59,833
No, I can't.

964
00:57:59,867 --> 00:58:01,067
What?

965
00:58:01,067 --> 00:58:02,767
I have the Russo
meeting tonight.

966
00:58:04,133 --> 00:58:05,167
Well, I--

967
00:58:05,200 --> 00:58:07,167
I'm sure he'd understand
if you canceled.

968
00:58:07,200 --> 00:58:08,367
Olivia...

969
00:58:09,633 --> 00:58:11,800
This is very important, 
 and you know that.

970
00:58:11,833 --> 00:58:13,333
-Max--
 -Olivia.

971
00:58:13,367 --> 00:58:19,333
I know this seems a bit unusual
but I have to make this dinner.

972
00:58:19,367 --> 00:58:21,500
Now, I'll talk to you 
 when I get home. All right?

973
00:58:23,100 --> 00:58:24,467
Okay.

974
00:58:24,500 --> 00:58:25,600
Okay.

975
00:58:28,067 --> 00:58:29,067
(phone bleeps)

976
00:58:33,900 --> 00:58:35,500
(dial tone)

977
00:58:37,067 --> 00:58:39,167
(crying)
Oh, God...

978
00:58:44,067 --> 00:58:45,900
(sniffs)
(exhales)

979
00:58:48,567 --> 00:58:49,767
(knocking on door)

980
00:58:52,067 --> 00:58:53,067
Can I come in?

981
00:58:53,700 --> 00:58:54,733
(bleep)

982
00:58:55,867 --> 00:58:57,933
I'm sorry about Aunt Ruth.

983
00:58:57,967 --> 00:59:00,233
-Are you alright?
-I'm fine.

984
00:59:00,267 --> 00:59:02,800
-I'm worried about you.
-Well, don't worry. I'm fine.

985
00:59:02,833 --> 00:59:05,333
I've been thinking about
making you a sign that says:

986
00:59:05,367 --> 00:59:07,533
"Why lie? I need a friend."

987
00:59:07,567 --> 00:59:08,767
-A what?
-Well, you know,

988
00:59:08,800 --> 00:59:09,800
like the homeless guy?

989
00:59:10,767 --> 00:59:12,367
Look, uh,

990
00:59:12,400 --> 00:59:15,067
I know that you've been through
a lot lately.

991
00:59:15,067 --> 00:59:18,433
But remember when you said that
man seemed naked and vulnerable?

992
00:59:18,467 --> 00:59:20,133
No secrets. Nothing to hide.

993
00:59:21,733 --> 00:59:23,967
Well, I think that's
you right now. And--

994
00:59:24,067 --> 00:59:25,467
Scarlett.

995
00:59:25,500 --> 00:59:27,967
I don't think this is
the time to go into this.

996
00:59:28,067 --> 00:59:30,667
I just hope you consider me
a friend. You know...

997
00:59:30,700 --> 00:59:32,800
I mean, someone you can talk
to if you really need to--

998
00:59:32,833 --> 00:59:35,100
Scarlett,
I'd like you to go out

999
00:59:35,133 --> 00:59:36,667
and close the door behind you.

1000
00:59:36,700 --> 00:59:38,200
Now this is a business,
remember?

1001
00:59:38,233 --> 00:59:40,700
I have work to do,
and you have work to do.

1002
00:59:44,567 --> 00:59:46,633
I assume you want me to
cancel the Russo dinner.

1003
00:59:46,667 --> 00:59:48,733
No. No, you can't do that.

1004
00:59:48,767 --> 00:59:49,933
It's too important.
You know that.

1005
00:59:49,967 --> 00:59:51,233
Yeah, um...

1006
00:59:52,233 --> 00:59:53,367
Okay.

1007
00:59:54,700 --> 00:59:56,067
(sighing)

1008
01:00:09,667 --> 01:00:10,833
(dial tone)

1009
01:00:13,867 --> 01:00:14,833
(dialing)

1010
01:00:25,967 --> 01:00:27,700
(line ringing)

1011
01:00:30,867 --> 01:00:34,100
Scarlett (over phone):
 Olivia, um, it's me.

1012
01:00:34,133 --> 01:00:35,267
We need to talk.

1013
01:00:36,500 --> 01:00:38,833
Something really weird's 
 going on with Max.

1014
01:00:38,867 --> 01:00:40,667
If you can, 
 would you try to meet me

1015
01:00:40,700 --> 01:00:42,700
tomorrow morning
at nine o'clock?

1016
01:00:42,733 --> 01:00:44,033
At the entrance to City Park.

1017
01:00:45,200 --> 01:00:46,767
Okay. Thanks. Bye.

1018
01:00:47,800 --> 01:00:49,200
(line goes dead)

1019
01:00:51,233 --> 01:00:52,267
Talk to me.

1020
01:00:53,133 --> 01:00:54,400
Oh, Tess...

1021
01:00:55,700 --> 01:00:56,800
I don't know where to start.

1022
01:00:56,833 --> 01:00:59,300
I feel like my whole
world is falling apart.

1023
01:01:00,467 --> 01:01:02,233
I don't even know why I'm here.

1024
01:01:02,267 --> 01:01:04,667
I mean, what, with Ruth's death
and all that's going on it's--

1025
01:01:04,700 --> 01:01:06,233
Don't beat yourself up.

1026
01:01:07,367 --> 01:01:08,967
You know what I really
can't figure out is

1027
01:01:09,067 --> 01:01:10,667
what is going on with Max.

1028
01:01:11,733 --> 01:01:13,233
Well, what happened last night?

1029
01:01:13,267 --> 01:01:14,467
We had this huge fight

1030
01:01:14,500 --> 01:01:15,600
at Carnegie's and
I walked out on him.

1031
01:01:15,633 --> 01:01:18,633
-Oh, no.
-Tess, I'm telling you,

1032
01:01:18,667 --> 01:01:21,367
even Scarlett thinks
he's been acting weird.

1033
01:01:21,400 --> 01:01:22,500
So what else?

1034
01:01:23,900 --> 01:01:25,167
Well you know when
you live with someone

1035
01:01:25,200 --> 01:01:26,700
a really long time and
there's certain things

1036
01:01:26,733 --> 01:01:27,967
you just know they wouldn't do?

1037
01:01:28,933 --> 01:01:30,800
Well, when Max and I
were first married,

1038
01:01:30,833 --> 01:01:32,467
I pointed out to him
in a crossword puzzle how

1039
01:01:32,500 --> 01:01:34,333
the letters LIV are the same as

1040
01:01:34,367 --> 01:01:36,633
-the Roman numeral 54.
-Mm-hmm.

1041
01:01:36,667 --> 01:01:38,500
And since we
live on 54th Street,

1042
01:01:38,533 --> 01:01:41,067
-Max started calling me Liv.
-Mm...

1043
01:01:41,067 --> 01:01:43,067
And then I told him how
much I hated that nickname,

1044
01:01:43,100 --> 01:01:44,767
and so he stopped.

