1360
01:18:01,733 --> 01:18:04,933
Well, to honest with you,
he was no angel.

1361
01:18:04,967 --> 01:18:06,367
That's not to say
he's still like that,

1362
01:18:06,400 --> 01:18:07,533
but, uh...

1363
01:18:07,567 --> 01:18:09,067
But what?

1364
01:18:10,067 --> 01:18:12,700
Look, I don't really
want to get involved.

1365
01:18:12,733 --> 01:18:13,833
Have a good day.

1366
01:18:13,867 --> 01:18:15,533
Wait, wait.

1367
01:18:15,567 --> 01:18:18,067
Mrs. Johnson, please.

1368
01:18:18,100 --> 01:18:20,567
Isn't there anything that you
can tell me about him?

1369
01:18:20,600 --> 01:18:22,667
Look, Mrs. Jordan,

1370
01:18:22,700 --> 01:18:24,900
I don't know what you want
and I don't know what you need,

1371
01:18:24,933 --> 01:18:26,533
but I'll say this:

1372
01:18:26,567 --> 01:18:28,333
some stones are better
left unturned.

1373
01:18:29,633 --> 01:18:32,800
And if you are unfortunate
enough to find him,

1374
01:18:32,833 --> 01:18:34,367
I'd be careful if I were you.

1375
01:18:44,267 --> 01:18:47,067
Tess, I'm telling you.
I've been sensing it all week.

1376
01:18:47,067 --> 01:18:48,667
I mean, everything
he does is just

1377
01:18:48,700 --> 01:18:50,500
a little bit off...

1378
01:18:50,533 --> 01:18:54,067
The anniversary, my nickname,
his reaction to Ruth's recovery.

1379
01:18:54,067 --> 01:18:57,167
His reaction to Ruth's death.
It isn't Max.

1380
01:18:57,200 --> 01:18:59,167
Even the sex is...

1381
01:18:59,200 --> 01:19:00,433
It's different, you know.

1382
01:19:00,467 --> 01:19:02,367
It's so intense
it's almost scary.

1383
01:19:03,667 --> 01:19:05,067
So what are you saying?

1384
01:19:07,200 --> 01:19:08,233
(sighs)

1385
01:19:10,133 --> 01:19:11,500
Max has a twin brother.

1386
01:19:13,533 --> 01:19:15,800
He survived the crash
and he's still alive.

1387
01:19:15,833 --> 01:19:17,633
He has a twin?

1388
01:19:17,667 --> 01:19:21,267
Look, I know this might sound
bizarre, but...

1389
01:19:21,300 --> 01:19:23,833
what if he somehow switched
places with my husband?

1390
01:19:23,867 --> 01:19:25,267
Okay.

1391
01:19:25,300 --> 01:19:26,533
It's very normal when you're
grieving to make things--

1392
01:19:26,567 --> 01:19:28,833
Tess, Tess, look. You know me!

1393
01:19:28,867 --> 01:19:30,367
You know how close
I am with Max!

1394
01:19:30,400 --> 01:19:31,367
I can feel this!

1395
01:19:32,467 --> 01:19:34,633
Even Jackson noticed it.
Scarlett noticed it, too--

1396
01:19:34,667 --> 01:19:37,600
Olivia, you are my best friend
and I love you dearly.

1397
01:19:37,633 --> 01:19:39,633
But I think you're way out of
the ballpark on this.

1398
01:19:39,667 --> 01:19:42,800
I know.
I know I must sound crazy.

1399
01:19:42,833 --> 01:19:45,833
There's gotta be some
explanation for this.

1400
01:19:45,867 --> 01:19:50,400
When was the last time that
I know I was with my husband?

1401
01:19:53,267 --> 01:19:54,767
It was the night of the funeral.

1402
01:19:55,833 --> 01:19:57,200
It was the night of the funeral,

1403
01:19:57,233 --> 01:19:59,333
and I definitely woke up with
him the next morning.

1404
01:19:59,367 --> 01:20:01,633
We have to go back to that day.
We have to go back to that day

1405
01:20:01,667 --> 01:20:03,567
and find out
every single thing he did.

1406
01:20:05,400 --> 01:20:06,500
I want to go to his office.

1407
01:20:10,800 --> 01:20:11,967
Okay.

1408
01:20:13,167 --> 01:20:14,267
Let's go.

1409
01:20:16,500 --> 01:20:18,633
Olivia: Take a right. His
parking space is right there.

1410
01:20:21,333 --> 01:20:23,233
There's his parking space. Stop.

1411
01:20:23,267 --> 01:20:24,467
Stop, stop, stop.

1412
01:20:25,400 --> 01:20:26,567
Okay, good. He's not here.

1413
01:20:26,600 --> 01:20:27,933
We're okay.

1414
01:20:27,967 --> 01:20:29,067
Park over there.

1415
01:20:36,800 --> 01:20:37,900
(elevator bell dings)

1416
01:20:57,567 --> 01:21:00,267
Okay, you stay out here
and keep watch.

1417
01:21:00,300 --> 01:21:01,433
I'll be right out.

1418
01:21:22,567 --> 01:21:23,933
(exhales)

1419
01:21:33,067 --> 01:21:34,400
East 54th Street?

1420
01:21:37,433 --> 01:21:38,600
(loudly)
Max!

1421
01:21:39,833 --> 01:21:41,533
Max, how are you?

1422
01:21:41,567 --> 01:21:43,067
Tess, well...

1423
01:21:43,900 --> 01:21:45,233
...to what do I owe
this pleasure?

1424
01:21:45,267 --> 01:21:49,133
Oh, just looking for Jackson.
Not here, huh?

1425
01:21:49,167 --> 01:21:50,933
No. No, I guess not.

1426
01:21:51,633 --> 01:21:52,800
Do you know where my wife is?

1427
01:21:52,833 --> 01:21:55,467
No. No, I haven't seen her.

1428
01:21:55,500 --> 01:21:58,400
Hey, you know, I've been
meaning to ask you,

1429
01:21:58,433 --> 01:22:00,067
how have you been,

1430
01:22:00,067 --> 01:22:02,667
you know, with everything
that's happened and all?

1431
01:22:02,700 --> 01:22:03,733
Fine.

1432
01:22:04,267 --> 01:22:05,400
Everything's fine.

1433
01:22:07,633 --> 01:22:09,733
Well, I wouldn't worry about
her too much.

1434
01:22:09,767 --> 01:22:12,567
I mean, she was fine
at the art gallery last night.

1435
01:22:12,600 --> 01:22:14,667
I mean, other than,
um, you know,

1436
01:22:14,700 --> 01:22:16,067
being upset about Aunt Ruth.

1437
01:22:16,833 --> 01:22:18,533
Yeah. Right, right.

1438
01:22:18,567 --> 01:22:19,700
Well, if you hear from her

1439
01:22:19,733 --> 01:22:21,167
would you have her
call me, please?

1440
01:22:21,200 --> 01:22:23,633
-Of course.
-Thanks, Tess.

1441
01:22:23,667 --> 01:22:24,800
Max...

1442
01:22:24,833 --> 01:22:26,433
Oh, hey, there you are.

1443
01:22:26,467 --> 01:22:27,867
I didn't expect
to find you here.

1444
01:22:28,767 --> 01:22:29,233
Honey, what...

1445
01:22:30,433 --> 01:22:32,767
-...what are you doing' here?
-I was just looking for you.

1446
01:22:32,800 --> 01:22:33,800
What's the matter with you?

1447
01:22:34,667 --> 01:22:36,667
Stu just got a call
from the police.

1448
01:22:37,867 --> 01:22:39,467
Scarlett's dead.

1449
01:22:39,500 --> 01:22:42,333
She was murdered last night.
They, uh...

1450
01:22:42,367 --> 01:22:43,600
...they just found her body.

1451
01:22:43,633 --> 01:22:45,867
-Oh, my God.
-When did this happen?

1452
01:22:45,900 --> 01:22:47,300
-I don't-- I don't know.
-The police are trying

1453
01:22:47,333 --> 01:22:48,400
to figure it out.

1454
01:22:51,067 --> 01:22:52,900
I can't-- I can't believe this.

1455
01:22:55,167 --> 01:22:57,800
Max, I'm, uh...
I'm really sorry.

1456
01:23:01,933 --> 01:23:05,133
Um, I'll go make
the phone calls and stuff.

1457
01:23:13,167 --> 01:23:14,633
You really should go home now.

1458
01:23:16,100 --> 01:23:17,233
Yeah, you're right.

1459
01:23:18,767 --> 01:23:20,067
I should go home.

1460
01:23:29,967 --> 01:23:32,067
(door opening)

1461
01:23:50,167 --> 01:23:51,300
Hello, Max.

1462
01:23:53,433 --> 01:23:54,600
How was your day?

1463
01:23:59,067 --> 01:24:01,300
I hope it's been
better than mine.

1464
01:24:01,333 --> 01:24:02,800
I'm not having a very good one.

1465
01:24:07,600 --> 01:24:09,467
We're gonna change
clothes now, Max.

1466
01:24:18,433 --> 01:24:20,800
You know, Mother always said
we had to learn to share.

1467
01:24:29,200 --> 01:24:32,200
We'd better hurry.
Time's wasting.

1468
01:24:48,800 --> 01:24:50,800
Our anniversary dinner.
Our anniv--

1469
01:24:52,300 --> 01:24:54,767
Our anniversary dinner
was on March 20th.

1470
01:24:56,533 --> 01:24:58,100
March, the third month.

1471
01:24:58,133 --> 01:25:00,733
320. 320 East 54th Street.

1472
01:25:01,767 --> 01:25:03,067
That's it.

1473
01:25:05,267 --> 01:25:06,900
(tires screech)

1474
01:25:29,167 --> 01:25:31,267
It's been nice getting
to know you, Max.

1475
01:25:33,667 --> 01:25:35,967
I can't tell you what the past
few days have meant to me.

1476
01:25:39,700 --> 01:25:42,233
My existence was kept
a secret from you.

1477
01:25:45,867 --> 01:25:49,067
I'm just sorry I had to be the
one to introduce myself first.

1478
01:25:52,833 --> 01:25:54,967
Our worlds have
always been apart...

1479
01:25:57,800 --> 01:26:00,367
...and now we must part again.

1480
01:26:00,400 --> 01:26:01,800
(siren wails in background)

1481
01:26:20,800 --> 01:26:22,067
I'm letting you go.

1482
01:26:36,600 --> 01:26:38,067
I can't do this anymore.

1483
01:26:55,367 --> 01:26:56,400
Do it.

1484
01:26:58,433 --> 01:26:59,633
That's what you'd like,
isn't it?

1485
01:27:07,067 --> 01:27:08,133
Do it.

1486
01:27:10,367 --> 01:27:12,067
I wouldn't give you
the satisfaction.

1487
01:27:14,333 --> 01:27:15,467
You're sick.

1488
01:27:15,500 --> 01:27:16,633
Sick!

1489
01:27:18,500 --> 01:27:19,800
You sick bastard!

1490
01:27:23,933 --> 01:27:25,067
I swear...

1491
01:27:47,500 --> 01:27:48,300
(screams)

1492
01:27:49,067 --> 01:27:50,267
(cocks gun)
Don't move!

1493
01:27:51,133 --> 01:27:52,233
Olivia...

1494
01:27:53,733 --> 01:27:55,133
Olivia, it's me.

1495
01:27:55,167 --> 01:27:56,567
I said don't move!

1496
01:27:57,233 --> 01:27:58,467
Where's my husband?

1497
01:28:06,733 --> 01:28:07,833
I'm your husband.

1498
01:28:09,700 --> 01:28:11,233
It's me, Max.

1499
01:28:11,267 --> 01:28:12,567
Stay away from me!

1500
01:28:13,533 --> 01:28:14,800
I know everything.

1501
01:28:16,500 --> 01:28:18,067
I know who you are!

1502
01:28:18,067 --> 01:28:20,100
You've got to believe me,
Olivia.

1503
01:28:20,133 --> 01:28:21,200
No...

1504
01:28:24,567 --> 01:28:25,700
Max!

1505
01:28:26,367 --> 01:28:27,500
Olivia...

1506
01:28:27,533 --> 01:28:28,567
Oh, my God!

1507
01:28:28,600 --> 01:28:29,900
Look what he's done to me.

1508
01:28:31,467 --> 01:28:32,933
Olivia, don't believe him.

1509
01:28:34,167 --> 01:28:35,467
It's me.

1510
